text.section:
An applicant shall show in the application to the satisfaction of the Board:
That the applicant will construct or operate a facility capable of producing ethanol or biodiesel;
That the applicant will invest or has invested substantial resources in the State in connection with the facility;
That the facility will constitute a permanent fixture in the State;
For an ethanol production facility, information demonstrating:
The production capacity of the facility; and
The quantity and availability of small grains and other suitable agricultural products in the vicinity of the production facility that may be used by the facility;
For a biodiesel production facility, information demonstrating:
The production capacity of the facility; and
The quantity and availability of soybean oil and other suitable bio-based oils in the vicinity of the production facility that may be used by the facility;
Information demonstrating:
The availability and cost of energy sufficient to operate the facility;
The availability of sufficient water and waste disposal systems for the facility;
The availability of sufficient labor and a qualified site manager for the facility; and
That the facility will meet all State and federal environmental standards;
Any proposed marketing agreements for the ethanol or biodiesel products;
A plan to give farmers in the State the opportunity to invest in the facility; and
That the applicant will meet any other requirement established by the Board.
